{"id":492,"date":"2020-10-26T05:37:33","date_gmt":"2020-10-26T05:37:33","guid":{"rendered":"http:\/\/amorgroupofhotels.com\/?p=492"},"modified":"2020-10-26T05:37:35","modified_gmt":"2020-10-26T05:37:35","slug":"6-lesser-known-beaches-of-goa","status":"publish","type":"post","link":"http:\/\/amorgroupofhotels.com\/6-lesser-known-beaches-of-goa\/","title":{"rendered":"6 Lesser known Beaches of Goa"},"content":{"rendered":"\n<p>Goa is famous for its beaches and some are so popular that you will see it most of the time crowded the entire year. Tourists looking for adventure, lots of busy restaurants, bistros and water sports in Goa flock around here.<br>These Beaches include the famous queen of Goa beach \u2013 Calangute, Baga, Candolim, Morjim in the North and Colva, Palolem in the South. But among the Goa beaches list, there are some unknown, less crowded beaches that one can visit for a relaxing getaway.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>Following are some of these \u201d Secret Beaches in Goa\u201d that one can plan to visit on their Goa trip.<br><strong> 1) Kakolem Beach<br><\/strong>Considered to be a perfect place for honeymoons, Kakolem Beach in the South is a small beach cove that tops among the secluded beaches in Goa.<br> As it is an isolated location, it does not offer any nightlife to the tourists.<br> Kakolem Beach is located at a distance of 29 kilometers from Margao.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>2) Kalacha Beach<br><\/strong>Located at around 35 kilometers from Panaji, Kalacha Beach in Pernem offers its visitors sweet water lagoon and occasionally bonfire by voyagers that will leave you a relaxed and piece of mind. You might be surprised by some wild visitors like monkeys and some exotic birds around the new water tidal pond near the overgrown, green slopes behind the sands.<br> One can see some beach parties and live music sessions by tourists.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>3) Hollant Beach<br><\/strong>Searching for a perfect sunrise view? then head to Hollant beach in South Goa. Approximately at a distance of 27 kilometers from Panaji is this enchanting beach.One can plan to swim in the water as the currents are not that strong here. Nestled along the foothills of the lush Western Ghats, Hollant beach offers beautiful views of merging of seawater and fresh water.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>4) Velsao Beach<br><\/strong>If you are in the South, this perfect picturesque landscape will attract you with its beauty. One can witness the flawless extends of white sand on this beach where one can walk and sunbathe. At a distance of 24.6 kilometers from Panaji, this is beach is known for natural scenic beauty. There are few restaurants and pubs that one can visit during the evenings for snacks and dinner.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>5) Butterfly Beach<br><\/strong>Butterfly beach is a small beach just north of Palolem in South Goa. The name it got is for being a spot for millions of butterflies flying over the hilltop blossoms. This beach is not so crowded, but it is not easy to reach this place. One cannot reach to this place with a bike due to dense forests.Once you reach the Palolem beach, hire a boat ride to reach to this island beach.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>6) Odxel beach<br><\/strong>Located at a distance of 10 km from Panjim, this clean, small and beautiful beach is favourite among the locals for being a picnic spot. The beach offers a tranquil place to simply unwind with your friends and family. Unlike the Hollant Beach, Odxel beach is not suitable for a swim due to rocks and current. To the close proximity to this beach is the Governor of Goa\u2019s resident, National Institute of Oceanography, Goa University and the International Centre Goa. A perfect beach for nature lovers.<\/p>\n","protected":false},"excerpt":{"rendered":"<p>Goa is famous for its beaches and some are so popular that you will see it most of the time crowded the entire year. Tourists looking for adventure, lots of busy restaurants, bistros and water sports in Goa flock around here.The